  "texts": [
    "That is, [Dr C [β], t S 0 (a)] = 0 for all a ∈ Tube S 0 and β ∈ End Z(C) (Θ ⊗m), where |Bd(Σ C)| = The same holds if t S 0 is replaced by t N for a decorated submanifold N ⊂ S 0.",
    "Proof: Let us write S = S 0.",
    "We first show Dr C [β], t S (a) = 0 for any a ∈ Tube S. On the orthogonal complement of the skein subspace H C the commutator vanishes because Dr C [β] annihilates H ⊥ C, and t S (a)H ⊥ C ⊂ H ⊥ C. It therefore remains to verify that the commutator vanishes on H C. Since Ψ C is an isomorphism of unitary Tube-modules it is sufficient to show that Ψ C -1 Dr C [β] Ψ C: C * (Σ C) → C * (Σ C) commutes with the Tube action ▷ 0 on C * corresponding under Ψ C to t S. But ▷ 0 acts only on the tensor factor C(X 0 → χ ⊗S 0) of C *, while Ψ C -1 Dr C [β] Ψ C acts as identity on that factor by definition.",
    "We conclude that Dr C [β], t S (a) = 0.",
    "Finally, let N ⊂ S 0 and a ∈ A(N)."
  ]
